.TH GEN-NETWORK "1" "December 2025" "gen-network 202208081523-git" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
gen-network \- Random network settings generator for testing and development
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B gen-network
[\fI\,OPTIONS\/\fR] [\fI\,COMMAND\/\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B gen-network
is a utility for generating random network-related values including MAC addresses, port numbers, IPv4 addresses, and IPv6 addresses. It is useful for testing, development, scripting, and configuration tasks where random but valid network values are needed.
.PP
The script generates cryptographically random values using /dev/urandom and validates them to ensure they are usable (e.g., ports that are not in use, IP addresses that are not reserved). It also displays the current system IP address for reference.
.PP
gen-network is designed for developers, system administrators, and testers who need quick access to random network values.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B mac
Generate a random MAC address in both dash-separated (00-60-2F-XX-XX-XX) and colon-separated (00:60:2F:XX:XX:XX) formats
.TP
.B port
Generate a random port number between 2000 and 65000, verified to not be in use
.TP
.B ipv4, ip4
Generate a random valid IPv4 address (excludes private and reserved ranges)
.TP
.B ipv6, ip6
Generate a random IPv6 address with a sample network prefix (2001:470:26:307)
.TP
.B all
Generate all types: port, IPv4, IPv6, and MAC address (default action)
