.SH USE CASES
.SS Development Testing
Generate random values for testing network code:
.PP
.RS 4
.EX
# Get a random port for test server
PORT=$(gen-network port | awk '{print $NF}')
./test-server --port $PORT
.EE
.RE
.SS Configuration Templates
Generate unique values for configuration:
.PP
.RS 4
.EX
# Generate MAC for virtual machine
MAC=$(gen-network mac | head -1 | awk '{print $NF}')
echo "MAC_ADDR=$MAC" >> vm-config.sh
.EE
.RE
.SS Docker/Container Setup
Generate network settings for containers:
.PP
.RS 4
.EX
# Random port mapping
HOST_PORT=$(gen-network port | awk '{print $NF}')
docker run -p $HOST_PORT:8080 myapp
.EE
.RE
.SS Network Simulation
Generate random addresses for testing:
.PP
.RS 4
.EX
# Generate test IP addresses
for i in {1..10}; do
  gen-network ipv4 --raw | awk '{print $NF}'
done
.EE
.RE
.SH TECHNICAL DETAILS
.SS Random Generation
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Uses /dev/urandom for cryptographically secure randomness
.IP \(bu 2
Port numbers verified with netstat to ensure availability
.IP \(bu 2
IPv4 addresses validated against RFC reserved ranges
.RE
.SS MAC Address Format
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Vendor prefix: 00:60:2F (3Com Corporation)
.IP \(bu 2
Last 3 octets: randomly generated
.IP \(bu 2
Locally administered bit: not set (globally unique format)
.RE
.SS Port Range
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Minimum: 2000 (above well-known ports)
.IP \(bu 2
Maximum: 65000 (below max 65535)
.IP \(bu 2
Excludes ports currently in use on system
.RE
.SH NOTES
.IP \(bu 2
Requires /dev/urandom for random number generation
.IP \(bu 2
Port checking requires netstat command
.IP \(bu 2
IPv4 generation excludes all private and reserved ranges
.IP \(bu 2
IPv6 uses sample Hurricane Electric tunnel broker prefix
.IP \(bu 2
